ome.smuggler.web.imports

Class ImportRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • ome.smuggler.web.imports.ImportRequest

  • public class ImportRequest
extends java.lang.Object
    Web clients use instances of this class to request an import. This is just a data transfer object whose sole purpose is to facilitate the transfer of information from the client to the server.

    • Field Detail

      • experimenterEmail

        public java.lang.String experimenterEmail
        The email address to send an outcome notification to. This should normally be the email address of the user who requested the import so that on completion the system can send them an email indicating success or failure to import the data.

      • targetUri

        public java.lang.String targetUri
        The URI of the file or directory containing the data to import. This is a mandatory field and must be either
        • a "file:" URI pointing to the file on the machine where the data to import sits (if the host part is missing, the path is assumed to be that of a file on the same machine where this server runs); or
        • if both client and server run on the same machine, a local path to the data to import.
        For now these are the only supported options, but, going forward, we will implement the means to resolve file locations across a network so that an import server may pull image data from multiple acquisition workstations.
        See Also:
        File URI scheme

      • omeroHost

        public java.lang.String omeroHost
        The hostname or IP address of the machine running the OMERO server in which the data will be imported. This is a mandatory field.

      • omeroPort

        public java.lang.String omeroPort
        The port of the OMERO server. This is an optional field and must parse to a non-negative integer if specified. Defaults to 4064.

      • sessionKey

        public java.lang.String sessionKey
        Mandatory field to identify the OMERO session to use for the import. The client must acquire a session before submitting an import request as this server will never accept user names and passwords to run an import. The client can close the session as soon as this import request is submitted to this web server.

      • name

        public java.lang.String name
        Optional field for the image or plate name to use.

      • description

        public java.lang.String description
        Optional field for the image or plate description to use.

      • datasetId

        public java.lang.String datasetId
        If the image is to be imported into an existing OMERO dataset, then this field specifies its ID; leave out otherwise. If this field is specified, then it must parse to a non-negative long. Also, this field and the screenId are mutually exclusive, it is only allowed to specify one.
        See Also:
        screenId

      • screenId

        public java.lang.String screenId
        If the image is to be imported into an existing OMERO screen, then this field specifies its ID; leave out otherwise. If this field is specified, then it must parse to a non-negative long. Also, this field and the datasetId are mutually exclusive, it is only allowed to specify one.
        See Also:
        datasetId

      • textAnnotations

        public java.lang.String[][] textAnnotations
        Any optional image annotations to attach to the image being imported. Each entry is an array-stored pair [namespace, text] with both strings having length at least one. Any entry not conforming to this format will cause a validation error.

      • annotationIds

        public java.lang.String[] annotationIds
        Any optional annotation ID's to attach to the image being imported. If given, this array must contain a list of values that parse to a non-negative long in order to pass validation.
